propmt.prompt: Should we have sufficient talent to keep growing our bioscience sector at current rates, or will we need access to additional workforce/talent? Please include impact and estimates over time.

response.text: A: Based on the data available in the EOS Data Repository, the current rate of growth in the bioscience sector is sustainable with the existing talent pool. However, to ensure continued growth over time, it is recommended that additional workforce and talent be accessed. This could include recruiting from other regions or countries, as well as investing in training and education programs to develop local talent. Additionally, it is important to ensure that there are sufficient resources available for research and development in order to keep up with industry trends.
